{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":"beer_can/crew/skippy","await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"","closed_at":null,"closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"ca9a0b891dd153d918dcb45cde4681fb8d8ed034004500505e2bacdf5f3c70b0","created_at":"2026-03-16T16:47:54Z","created_by":"beer_can/crew/skippy","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Rename Gastown's Mad Max themed concepts into intuitive names. Gabrielle sparked the idea — themed names make onboarding hard. Option A (descriptive) is the base rename set. Coppertown is the locked project name. Rosetta Stone doc created at docs/coppertown-rosetta-stone.md. Open: refining 7 specific mappings (Hub, Lead, Merge Queue, Partner, Blueprint, Scratch Task, Standing Order).","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"bc-79d.1","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"Rosetta Stone doc at docs/coppertown-rosetta-stone.md is complete with full mapping tables. 7 mappings still under discussion: (1) Town — keeping Town is leading option since it's baked into the Coppertown name, (2) Lead for Mayor — may undersell the role, (3) Merge Queue vs Integrator for Refinery, (4) Partner vs keeping Crew, (5) Blueprint for Protomolecule — strong candidate, (6) Scratch Task for Wisp — ambiguous, (7) Auto-Execute Rule vs Standing Order for GUPP. Fire is out, Assign stays. Key insight from latest discussion: renaming Town breaks the Coppertown project name metaphor — likely keeping Town as-is.\n--- Progress update (2026-03-20) ---\n\nRESOLVED decisions (locked in doc):\n1. Town stays \"Town\" — already clear, baked into Coppertown name\n2. Mayor stays \"Mayor\" — intuitive in Town context\n3. Refinery → \"Integrator\" — Merge Queue was too narrow\n4. Crew → \"Team\" (member = \"Teammate\") — scored 4G 0R, beat Partner on pluralization\n5. Fire removed — Assign is sufficient\n6. Formula → \"Concept\", Protomolecule → \"Blueprint\", Molecule → \"Workflow\" — Concept/Blueprint distinction is clear (unlike Template/Blueprint which felt synonymous)\n7. CLI: copper/ct (hub) + task/tk (tasks) — long forms for docs, short for daily use. gt/bd kept as legacy aliases.\n\nSTILL OPEN:\n- Message vs. Mail (#3)\n- Scratch Task vs. Temp Task for Wisp (#4)\n- Kitchen/Yard cherry-picks — Heard, Ticket, Punch List (#5)\n- GUPP naming — Auto-Execute Rule vs Standing Order (from earlier session)\n- \"track\" as alternative CLI name for bd/task — train metaphor emerged (Track/Station/Depot/Manifest maps well to beads concepts). Question: does Coppertown want ANY metaphor or purely descriptive? Train theme is accessible but still a theme. Also avoids Taskwarrior collision on \"task\" binary name.","original_size":null,"owner":"70168+kingb@users.noreply.github.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"in_progress","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Coppertown: Intuitive Gastown — concept rename project","updated_at":"2026-03-20T15:56:41Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
